  <summary>1/31/2001--Introduced.
Parents Know Best Act of 2001 - Amends the Elementary and Secondary Education Act of 1965 (ESEA) to require parental notification and consent prior to enrollment of a child in a bilingual education program or a special alternative instructional program for limited English proficient students, if such program is assisted under ESEA.</summary>
